 sun\nSP.\nWhere everything starts and everything ends\nin a place where everything can change\nthe tablet hides behind a bush\nSW.\nWhere the air is glacial and lights are blinking\nthe key is found in the frigid waters\non a far island\nVE.\nWhere one can review knowledge\none diorama is different than the others\nas its base is mysteriously engraved"}
{"id": "1358", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1358", "title": "Artifact Key", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Items%23Boss\"&gt;boss item&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2. It is randomly dropped by enemies in &lt;a href=\"Bulwark%27s%20Ambry\"&gt;Bulwark's Ambry&lt;/a&gt; during an Artifact Trial. They are used to interact with and damage the , which is otherwise completely impervious to normal damage. When used, all Artifact Keys in the player's inventory, as well as those still on the field, are consumed, preventing the player from stockpiling them.\nThe Artifact Key's drop chance is not affected by the or , and it will drop even if the is not enabled.\nIt is one of few items that the has no effect on. Though a Yellow Command Essence will drop, it cannot be transformed into any item except the Artifact Key."}
