{"id": "389", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=389", "title": "H3AD-5T v2", "text": "The is an &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2.\nAs the holder falls, they can \"lock on\" to the nearest enemy by holding the \"interact\" key (default \"E\" on keyboard). This causes them to fall much faster than normal, and when they hit the ground, they create an explosion whose damage and size scale with the distance they fell. The damage dealt ranges from 1000%-10000% in a 5m-100m radius, and the explosion takes 10 seconds (\"-50% per stack\") to recharge. \nWhile the explosive ability is ready, the H3AD-5T v2 also increases the player's jump height.\nAdditionally, the H3AD-5T v2 negates \"all\" fall damage taken, regardless of whether the explosive ability is ready or not.\nMath.\nThe cooldown is determined by the formula formula_1, with \"x\" being the amount of ."}
{"id": "390", "revid": "51490531", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=390", "title": "Halcyon Seed", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Items%23Boss\"&gt;boss item&lt;/a&gt; introduced in the \"&lt;a href=\"Early%20Access%20Scorched%20Acres%20Content%20Update\"&gt;Scorched Acres Update&lt;/a&gt;\", dropped by defeating at &lt;a href=\"Gilded%20Coast\"&gt;Gilded Coast&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon beginning a &lt;a href=\"Teleporter%23Teleporter%20Event\"&gt;Teleporter Event&lt;/a&gt;, the player will lose their Halcyon Seed and Aurelionite will spawn as an ally. It will fight for the player until the Teleporter is charged, at which point it will instantly die. The player will retrieve their Halcyon Seed when Aurelionite dies (regardless of whether it died at the end of the Teleporter Event or was killed in some other way). In multiplayer, players who die after Aurelionite is summoned will still recover their Halcyon Seeds when Aurelionite dies.\nThis item stacks based on the total amount held by all players combined (items held by do not count), similarly to the . Each Halcyon Seed beyond the first gives Aurelionite additional damage and an additional 100% health.\nIf the player is fighting the and is in phase 4, Aurelionite will spawn and help the player."}
{"id": "2859", "revid": "51490531", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2859", "title": "Halcyon Shrine", "text": "The Halcyon Shrine is one of the &lt;a href=\"Interactibles%23Shrines\"&gt;Shrines&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2, added in the &lt;a href=\"Seekers%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Seekers of the Storm&lt;/a&gt; expansion.\nUpon interacting with the shrine, a pillar of stone rises up and the players' &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; is slowly taken away while they are in its vicinity. This gold is used to charge the shrine up, visually indicated by the pillar of stone turning to gold, while periodically spawn around the shrine. Once the Halcyon Shrine is fully charged, or the players interact with it once it has charged at least a minimum percentage, a will spawn. Defeating the Halcyonite will spawn a number of rewards for each player before opening a portal indicated by the orb orbiting it.\nCredits.\nThe shrine requires 300 gold, scaled by &lt;a href=\"Difficulty%23The%20Math%20of%20Scaling%20Difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt;, in order to fully charge. However, at 75 and 150 it crosses the minimum and medium thresholds, indicated by a visual and auditory effect. Once the minimum threshold has been crossed, the players can \"pray\" to the shrine by interacting with it again to terminate the charging process.\nThe shrine drains 1 gold every 0.2 seconds from up to 4 players that are within a 30-meter radius. For a single player it requires 60 seconds to fully charge it.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Directors%23The%20Combat%20Directors\"&gt;Combat Director&lt;/a&gt; related to the shrine has 100 credits, also scaled by difficulty. Once the shrine is activated it spends all of its credits spawning Stone Golems in any required numbers and Elite modifiers. It also spawns another round of Stone Golems with the same number of credits when crossing the minimum and medium thresholds respectively. At a difficulty value of 1 killing all the Stone Golems will net the player 63 gold, or 21% of the total gold required to fully charge the shrine. However, as the difficulty increases the gold earned from the Stone Golems will solely be sufficient to fully pay off the shrine's requirements.\nAurelionite Fragment.\nOnce the Halcyonite has been killed, the shrine will drop a reward similar to a &lt;a href=\"Void%20Potential\"&gt;Void Potential&lt;/a&gt; for each player, where the higher the charging threshold has been crossed before summoning the Halcyonite, the more items will be available.\nThe items for any of these choices are selected from two mutually exclusive pools, where pool A are any items in the category and pool B any items not in that category. The rarity weights for both of the pools are: \nThe rewards for each threshold are summarised as follows\nIf instead the is enabled, n-2 command cubes will be dropped, where n is the number of item choices for each threshold, i.e., 1 for minimum, 2 for medium, and 3 command cubes for the maxed out threshold. If the shrine has not been fully charged, items from pool A will be selected, else from pool B. While with the Artifact of Command the player can choose any item, whether an item is selected from pool A or pool B affects the rarity distribution due to the &lt;a href=\"Chests%23Drop%20Chance%20Bias\"&gt;drop chance bias&lt;/a&gt;, which in turn affects how likely a common, , or command cube will be dropped.\nPortals.\nThe Halcyon Shrine can spawn either a Green or a Gold portal. The requirements for spawning either portal are as follow: \nGreen Portal.\nThe Green Portal takes the player to a set of predefined Environments based on the stage it has spawned in. Stage 1 Environments lead to , Stage 2 Environments to , and Stage 3 Environments to . Once the portal has been taken, any other Halcyon Shrines that spawn will spawn a Gold portal, allowing the player to acquire on the way to fighting the . in this case will also spawn a Green Portal to allow the player to return back to the Colossus Path after this detour, but only if the stage the player has come from is a Stage 1-3."}
{"id": "2907", "revid": "49014538", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2907", "title": "Halcyonite", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Monsters\"&gt;Monster&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2, added in the &lt;a href=\"Seekers%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Seekers of the Storm&lt;/a&gt; expansion. They are part of the monster family, but outside of that event they only spawn after &lt;a href=\"Mechanics%23Looping\"&gt;looping&lt;/a&gt;. They also spawn as a elite upon the completion of the &lt;a href=\"Halcyon%20Shrine\"&gt;Halcyon Shrine&lt;/a&gt; event.\nSkills &amp; Behavior.\nAny single instance of damage that deals more than 15% of the Halcyonite's total health will stun it and interrupt its attacks or movement. Whirlwind is an exception to this (see &lt;a href=\"%23Notes\"&gt;Notes&lt;/a&gt; for further details).\nPrimary: Sword Thrust.\nThe Halcyonite pulls its right arm back and then thrusts the sword forward dealing 150% with a &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;proc coefficient&lt;/a&gt; of 1.0 while pushing the target away with a force of 2000. The attack has a medium reach forward with 24m. It is also very quick with very little telegraphing, lasting only 1 second and scaling with &lt;a href=\"Damage%23Attack%20Speed\"&gt;attack speed&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis skill has a cooldown of 5 seconds.\nSecondary: Triple Laser Attack.\nThis is a very similar, but upgraded version of the , where instead it fires 3 beams in total, one every 0.5 seconds. All 3 beams are fired at the same location without further tracking the target.\nWhile the phase of firing the laser lasts for 2 seconds and it scales with attack speed, it cannot be reduced to less than 1 second even with enough attack speed since all 3 shots are required to be fired.\nThis skill has a cooldown of 10 seconds, which starts the moment the first laser is fired.\nUtility: Whirlwind.\nThe Halcyonite raises its sword and performs a downwards swipe before starting to spin with its sword, dealing 90% damage with a proc coefficient of 0.2 every second for 5 seconds. Technically the attack spawns an area-of-effect projectile similar to the blazing pool which simply follows the Halcyonite, insted of a simple hitbox like the one in charge attack. As a result can actually disarm the attack even though the spinning animation will continue.\nThis skill has a cooldown of 10 seconds.\nSpecial: Sword Swipe.\nThe Halcyonite raises its sword and performs a downwards swipe dealing 150% damage with a proc coefficient of 1.0. Similar to the Sword Thrust it has the same duration, but the swipe extends 11m forward and 20m across.\nThis skill has a cooldown of 3 seconds."}
{"id": "392", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=392", "title": "Happiest Mask", "text": "The Happiest Mask is a &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2. \nWhen the holder kills an enemy, there is a 7% chance that a ghost of that enemy will spawn as an ally, with greatly increased attack strength. The chance for this to happen is affected by &lt;a href=\"Luck\"&gt;Luck&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe ghost inherits all behaviors of the original monster. The level of the ghost equals the \"ambient\" level of the run (the same one enemies use, displayed at the top right on the HUD) or the player team level, whichever is greater.\nGhosts do not take damage through any normal means; instead, their health drops by a fixed percentage every second. Each ghost normally lasts 30 seconds (\"+30s per stack\"), though this can be prolonged if they are healed."}
{"id": "393", "revid": "39719838", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=393", "title": "Hardlight Afterburner", "text": "The Hardlight Afterburner is an &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2. \nThe holder gains an extra 2 (\"+2 per stack\") charges of their utility skill, and the cooldown of their utility skill is reduced by 33%."}
