{"id": "459", "revid": "52515586", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=459", "title": "Modding", "text": "Modding the game is currently possible on PC. This page serves as an entry into the world of &lt;a href=\"Risk%20of%20Rain%202\"&gt;Risk of Rain 2&lt;/a&gt; modding and installing mods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Developer%20Console\"&gt;Developer Console&lt;/a&gt; can be accessed by hitting codice_1 on the US key layout.\nThe modding wiki can be found &lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/risk-of-thunder/R2Wiki/wiki\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.\nInstalling Mods.\n\"Note that the programs listed here are not officially supported by devs, but they are cool with modding.\"\nIt is highly recommended that you use &lt;a href=\"https%3A//thunderstore.io/package/ebkr/r2modman/\"&gt;r2ModMan&lt;/a&gt;, which is a mod manager that can download mods directly from &lt;a href=\"https%3A//thunderstore.io/\"&gt;Thunderstore&lt;/a&gt;, a site which contains the vast majority of Risk of Rain 2 mods. Alternatively, you can install them manually:\nFor tech support regarding mods not working correctly, you can ask for help in the modding Discord found on the top of the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//thunderstore.io/\"&gt;Thunderstore page&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2389", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2389", "title": "Molotov (6-Pack)", "text": "The is an &lt;a href=\"Items%23Equipment\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2, added in the \"&lt;a href=\"Survivors%20of%20the%20Void\"&gt;Survivors of the Void&lt;/a&gt;\" expansion.\nWhen activated, it launches a large molotov projectile (which is affected by gravity) which explodes upon impact or after 2 seconds, splitting into 6 smaller molotovs with the same lifetime. However, the smaller projectiles explode only upon impact with terrain, bouncing off from any enemies in their path. Both the large and small projectiles deal 250% damage with a &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;proc coefficient&lt;/a&gt; of 1.0 in a 7m radius with &lt;a href=\"Damage%23Damage%20Falloff\"&gt;no falloff&lt;/a&gt;, while inflicting enemies. The smaller projectiles leave behind lingering fire pools that deal 100% damage every 0.5 seconds with a &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;proc coefficient&lt;/a&gt; of 0.5. The fire pools last for 7 seconds."}
