{"id": "470", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=470", "title": "Newt Altars", "text": " are &lt;a href=\"interactables\"&gt;interactables&lt;/a&gt; that can be found on every standard &lt;a href=\"Environments\"&gt;Environment&lt;/a&gt;, usually hidden or in hard-to-reach areas. There are 3 to 5 possible Newt Altar spawn locations per stage.\nDonating to the Newt Altar will cause a Blue Orb to appear at the &lt;a href=\"Teleporter\"&gt;Teleporter&lt;/a&gt;, spawning a Blue Portal once the Teleporter is charged. Entering the Blue Portal will take the player to the . \nNewt Altars cannot be activated after the &lt;a href=\"Teleporter%23Teleporter%20Event\"&gt;Teleporter Event&lt;/a&gt; is completed.\nIt is possible, though rare, for 2 Newt Altars to spawn on the same Environment; however, only 1 of the 2 Altars can be interacted with and does not result in any additional gameplay changes. Sometimes no Newt Altar is spawned, although it is very rare to occur.\nTitanic Plains.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Titanic%20Plains%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Titanic Plains&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nDistant Roost.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Distant%20Roost%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Distant Roost&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nSiphoned Forest.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Siphoned%20Forest%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Siphoned Forest&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nVerdant Falls &amp; Viscous Falls.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Verdant%20Falls%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Verdant Falls&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Viscous%20Falls%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Viscous Falls&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nThe Newt Altars in Viscous Falls are the same as in Verdant Falls, except for one spawn spot missing.\nShattered Abodes &amp; Disturbed Impact.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Shattered%20Abodes%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Shattered Abodes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Disturbed%20Impact%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Disturbed Impact&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nThe Newt Altars in Disturbed Impact are totally different from the ones in Shattered Abodes.\nAbandoned Aqueduct.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Aqueduct%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Abandoned Aqueduct&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nWetland Aspect.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Wetland%20Aspect%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Wetland Aspect&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nAphelian Sanctuary.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Aphelian%20Sanctuary%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Aphelian Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nReformed Altar.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Reformed%20Altar%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Reformed Altar&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nRallypoint Delta.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Rallypoint%20Delta%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Rallypoint Delta&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nScorched Acres.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Scorched%20Acres%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Scorched Acres&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nSulfur Pools.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Sulfur%20Pools%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Sulfur Pools&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nTreeborn Colony &amp; Golden Dieback.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Treeborn%20Colony%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Treeborn Colony&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Dieback%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Golden Dieback&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nThe Newt Altars in Golden Dieback are the same as in Treeborn Colony.\nAbyssal Depths.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Abyssal%20Depths%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Abyssal Depths&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nSiren's Call.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Siren%27s%20Call%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Siren's Call&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nSundered Grove.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Sundered%20Grove%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Sundered Grove&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nSky Meadow.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Sky%20Meadow%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Sky Meadow&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nHelminth Hatchery.\n\"See: &lt;a href=\"Helminth%20Hatchery%23Newt%20Altars\"&gt;Helminth Hatchery&lt;/a&gt; for detailed descriptions\"\nNotes.\nNewt Altars cannot spawn in the &lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt;."}
