{"id": "504", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=504", "title": "Radio Scanner", "text": "\"Not to be confused with , an equipment that scans for interactables\"\nThe (also known as Radar Tower, Environment Scanner) is an &lt;a href=\"Interactables\"&gt;interactable&lt;/a&gt; that can spawn on all &lt;a href=\"Environments\"&gt;Environments&lt;/a&gt;, except &lt;a href=\"Environments%23Hidden%20Realms\"&gt;Hidden Realms&lt;/a&gt;. When purchased, the entire stage will be scanned, similarly to the , and the Environment Data of the corresponding stage will be added to the player's Logbook.\nOnce the Environment Data of a stage has been acquired, the Radio Scanner will never spawn again on that stage. In multiplayer, having at least one member of the party who doesn't possess the Environment Data of a stage will allow the corresponding Radio Scanner to spawn."}
{"id": "2185", "revid": "49014538", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2185", "title": "Railgunner", "text": " is a playable &lt;a href=\"Survivors\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2, unlocked by default in the &lt;a href=\"Survivors%20of%20the%20Void\"&gt;Survivors of the Void&lt;/a&gt; expansion.\nA lethal and skillful markswoman, the Railgunner fights with her eponymous railgun. In combination with powerful piercing shots and smart homing rounds, Railgunner has incredible long-range damage output and decent crowd control options. Her signature ability is the incredibly powerful, all-or-nothing Supercharge that can devastate even the strongest of enemies in a single shot.\nBehaviors.\n\"For an explanation of how these behaviors are implemented read about &lt;a href=\"Enemy%20AI\"&gt;Enemy AI&lt;/a&gt;. This section only applies when the character is controlled by AI.\"\nTips.\nWeak Points.\nWeak Point locations vary based on the type of monster and are consistent across all enemies of that type."}
