{"id": "2201", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2201", "title": "Shipping Request Form", "text": "The is an &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2, added in the \"&lt;a href=\"Survivors%20of%20the%20Void\"&gt;Survivors of the Void&lt;/a&gt;\" expansion. \nWhen entering a new stage, if any player has this item, a &lt;a href=\"Chests%23Crashed%20Multishop%20%22Delivery%22\"&gt;Crashed Multishop \"Delivery\"&lt;/a&gt; will spawn somewhere in the stage (one per player who has a Shipping Request Form). The \"delivery\" is a burning Multishop Terminal which is different from a normal one in a few ways: it costs \"no\" &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; to use, it has only 2 choices instead of the usual 3, and one of those 2 choices is a question mark icon (meaning the item of that rarity is unknown).\nMath.\nThe weight for each tier of item is calculated as follows:\nWhere codice_4 is the amount of Shipping Request Form.\nTo calculate the chance for a tier, add together all weights then divide that tier's weight by the total sum of all weights.\nFor example, if a player has 2 Shipping Request Form items, then the weights are 0.79 (common), 0.2 * 2 = 0.4 (uncommon), 0.01 * 2^2 = 0.04 (legendary). Then, the chance an item is legendary is 0.04 / (0.79 + 0.4 + 0.04) = 0.04 / 1.23, or approximately 0.0325, around 3%.\nThe table below shows the probabilities calculates for each value of codice_4. Note however that each delivery includes 2 choices. See &lt;a href=\"%23At%20least%201%20Legendary\"&gt;the section below for odds of at least one legendary.&lt;/a&gt;\nAt least 1 Legendary.\nEach item tier is independent of each other, but each delivery drop contains 2 items. You can calculate the probability of getting \"at least\" one item from a tier by using the complement: codice_6, where codice_7 is the probability of getting at least one that tier (shown above).\nFor example, with a stack of 3, the chance of one item being chosen as legendary is 6% = 0.06. The chance that it is \"not\" legendary is codice_8, so the chance that \"both\" are not legendary is codice_9. The complement of this is the chance that at least one is legendary: codice_10, roughly 11.5%.\nThe table below shows the probability that at least one item will appear a given stack of Shipping Request Form."}
{"id": "523", "revid": "41355612", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=523", "title": "Shrine of Blood", "text": "The Shrine of Blood is one of the &lt;a href=\"Interactibles%23Shrines\"&gt;Shrines&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2. Upon activation, the player will sacrifice a percentage of their HP to receive &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;. Generated gold is equal to half of the HP taken (e.g. 50 HP yields 25 gold). Upon purchase the HP cost is scaled by formula_1 and it can be purchased up to 3 times."}
{"id": "524", "revid": "24513582", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=524", "title": "Shrine of Chance", "text": "The Shrine of Chance is one of the &lt;a href=\"Interactibles%23Shrines\"&gt;Shrines&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2. It is shaped like a . Upon purchase, the player will have a chance to receive an &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; of a random rarity or a random equipment.\nThe base cost is $17, increasing by 40% with each activation. Receiving two items from a Shrine of Chance will prevent any further interaction with it. However, until both items are obtained, there is no limit\u2014save the amount of gold in the player's possession\u2014to the number of times a Shrine of Chance can be activated.\nMath.\nThe possible chains of independent random binary events where termination occurs after two successes can be represented as a tree formula_1, where\nformula_2\nThe expected cost of getting 2 items out of a Shrine of Chance is then formula_3, where\nformula_4\nformula_5 here represents the expected cost of getting formula_6 items out of a Shrine of Chance as a multiple of the current cost of activating the shrine. Successive simplification gives\nformula_7\nThis means that getting one item out of an unused Shrine of Chance is initially expected to be about 1.8 times as expensive as a small chest for a slightly rarer reward on average; emptying a Shrine of Chance costs on average about 1.5 times as much as opening two large chests for a more common reward."}
