{"id": "531", "revid": "55634805", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=531", "title": "Silence Between Two Strikes", "text": "The Silence Between Two Strikes is an &lt;a href=\"Items%23Elite%20Equipment\"&gt;Elite equipment&lt;/a&gt; in Risk of Rain 2. It can only be found as a rare drop from an &lt;a href=\"Monsters%23Overloading\"&gt;Elite&lt;/a&gt;. The drop chance is 1/4000 from each Overloading Elite, but this chance is affected by the and .\nA player equipped with the Silence Between Two Strikes gains the power of an Overloading Elite; 50% of their health is replaced by &lt;a href=\"Health%23Shield\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, and their attacks attach lightning bombs to enemies, which explode after a brief pause dealing 50% &lt;a href=\"Damage%23.27Base.27%20vs.%20.27Total.27%20Damage\"&gt;total damage&lt;/a&gt;. The bombs do not have a proc coefficient. \nAlthough the Silence Between Two Strikes is held in the equipment slot, it works passively and cannot be activated. Equipment cooldown reduction and additional equipment charges from do not affect its behavior."}
