{"id": "1921", "revid": "39719838", "url": "https://riskofrain2.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1921", "title": "UES Safe Travels", "text": "The UES \"Safe Travels\" is a spacefaring vessel in Risk of Rain 2, commanded by the .\nDescription.\nSome time after the events of , the \"Safe Travels\" arrived in orbit of &lt;a href=\"Petrichor%20V\"&gt;Petrichor V&lt;/a&gt; on a rescue mission to determine what became of the UES \"Contact Light\", locate any surviving crew, and salvage its valuable cargo. Given the diverse personnel on board, who make up the majority of the game's &lt;a href=\"Survivors\"&gt;Survivors&lt;/a&gt;, it remains a possibility that the rescue mission is only one part of the \"Safe Travels\"' reason for traveling to the hostile world. \nVarious downed rescue craft, ostensibly originating from the \"Safe Travels\", can be found throughout the game's &lt;a href=\"Environments\"&gt;Environments&lt;/a&gt;, apparently recent given the wrecks' still-smoldering state. An ill-fated expedition to the planet's moon &lt;a href=\"Commencement\"&gt;Commencement&lt;/a&gt; serves as the Survivors' means of escape at the game's conclusion via the still-functioning dropship initially detained on the moon's surface.\nDespite its occupants starting the game by arriving from within an &lt;a href=\"Escape%20Pod\"&gt;Escape Pod&lt;/a&gt;, the UES \"Safe Travels\" appears to be functional, as the Captain is able to call for support planetside with his various abilities. Given the fate of behind the \"Contact Light\"'s crash, the orbit of Petrichor V is apparently safe."}
